28:00.680 --> 28:02.216
- Keep going.
- That's all I know.

28:02.390 --> 28:05.006
Oh, come on.
I know you know more.

28:05.220 --> 28:08.519
I was 15 when they died.
Why would I know anything more?

28:09.100 --> 28:10.931
And why do you think
that there's more to know?

28:11.100 --> 28:12.340
And why do you care?

28:12.520 --> 28:14.932
- Because you are not Danny Rand.
- Yes, I am.

28:15.110 --> 28:17.396
Show me a DNA test
that proves you're a Rand.

28:18.690 --> 28:21.193
- I have no living relatives.
- A fingerprint test.

28:22.240 --> 28:24.196
I... I was ten when we crashed.

28:24.530 --> 28:27.237
- I never had fingerprints taken.
- Then you've got nothing.

28:27.620 --> 28:29.611
Oh, man. You know what?

28:29.790 --> 28:32.281
You were a dick as a kid,
and you're still a dick now.

28:32.500 --> 28:35.458
- You don't know anything about me.
- No.

28:36.460 --> 28:40.089
You used to lock me in the freezer
at the Rand cafeteria.

28:41.260 --> 28:42.625
At one of the company picnics...

28:43.180 --> 28:45.796
You put a dead frog in my sandwich.

28:47.010 --> 28:50.639
You would kick me in the balls every
chance you had.

28:51.930 --> 28:53.181
This sound familiar?

28:58.730 --> 28:59.890
None of that is true.

29:00.480 --> 29:02.232
Yes, it is.

29:02.490 --> 29:05.982
I can only wonder what it's like inside
that crazy little head of yours.

29:08.330 --> 29:10.787
You wanna know what it's like? Hmm?

29:12.000 --> 29:13.615
It feels like this...

29:17.000 --> 29:19.332
When you're a ten-year-old boy
and you watch your mother die...

29:20.800 --> 29:23.621
And you know you and your father are next,
it feels like this!

29:27.260 --> 29:29.421
You're crazy. Yeah! Yeah, maybe.

29:30.600 --> 29:32.670
Stop this.

29:32.850 --> 29:34.010
Stop.

29:34.980 --> 29:35.969
Stop the car!

29:37.650 --> 29:38.639
Hold on, Danny!

29:38.810 --> 29:39.765
Oh, my God!

29:40.020 --> 29:41.772
Stop the car!

29:41.940 --> 29:43.931
Stop the car!

30:00.040 --> 30:01.701
I'm... I'm sorry. I...

30:02.670 --> 30:03.955
I... I didn't mean to...

30:04.920 --> 30:06.000
This isn't over.

30:08.390 --> 30:10.711
Oh... I know.

30:29.320 --> 30:30.560
I thought you might be hungry.

30:31.950 --> 30:33.486
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

30:35.620 --> 30:36.826
Chicken parm.

30:37.870 --> 30:39.280
The Italian deli on Bleecker.

30:39.750 --> 30:41.661
They throw 'em out
at the end of the night.

30:42.880 --> 30:45.166
Plenty of food if you know where to look.

30:46.220 --> 30:47.710
That's where it all went wrong.

30:50.720 --> 30:52.039
Where all what went wrong?

30:53.890 --> 30:55.130
All of mankind.

30:57.770 --> 30:58.930
It's true.

31:01.150 --> 31:02.890
For, like, a couple million years...

31:03.610 --> 31:05.430
We were all hunters and gatherers.

31:06.860 --> 31:08.270
Life was good.

31:10.030 --> 31:13.443
People grew strong and tall
and lived into their 705.

31:14.910 --> 31:16.241
Then, like, 10,000 years ago,

31:16.410 --> 31:18.617
they all got hit with the idiot stick
and decided to start...

31:20.120 --> 31:23.123
Farmin', build cities.

31:23.290 --> 31:24.291
And everything went to shit.

31:25.460 --> 31:26.757
- Yeah.
- Not me, though.

31:26.920 --> 31:28.581
No way, man.

31:28.760 --> 31:31.172
I'ma stay true to my purpose.

31:31.340 --> 31:33.092
I'm a... I'm a hunter-gatherer.

31:34.430 --> 31:35.556
You're lucky, then.

31:37.140 --> 31:40.018
Buddha said, "Your purpose in life
is to find your purpose."

31:42.150 --> 31:43.640
Sure, that makes sense.

31:44.230 --> 31:45.219
Yeah.

31:46.570 --> 31:47.855
What's your purpose?

31:52.450 --> 31:54.736
To protect K'un-Lun from all oppression.

31:56.120 --> 31:58.190
Honour the sacrifice
of Shou-Lao the Undying.

32:03.500 --> 32:04.740
Well, okay then.

32:09.970 --> 32:12.677
Just remember to have fun along the way.

32:13.590 --> 32:14.887
All right, man.

32:15.180 --> 32:17.091
- Thanks for the food.
- Yep.

32:34.240 --> 32:35.229
Great.

32:37.330 --> 32:39.230
Thank you, guys. That was a lovely class.

32:39.410 --> 32:41.071
Please take some flyers.

32:41.710 --> 32:44.201
Pass them around,
invite your friends to take a class.

32:44.330 --> 32:45.877
We need to get more students in here.

32:45.960 --> 32:46.870
Oh, also...

32:46.960 --> 32:50.293
Thursday nights will be closed
for AA meetings.

32:50.670 --> 32:52.126
They pay more than you do.

32:52.630 --> 32:54.291
Otherwise this place is closing.

33:09.150 --> 33:10.185
Hi.

33:11.650 --> 33:12.890
Here for a lesson?

33:14.360 --> 33:15.736
What can $2 get me?

33:17.870 --> 33:19.235
Cup of coffee down the street?

33:19.410 --> 33:21.696
Hmm. I never had coffee before.

33:23.500 --> 33:26.037
Or maybe a pair of flip-flops
at one of the stalls.

33:27.080 --> 33:28.240
Down the street.

33:28.880 --> 33:30.199
Oh. I'm, uh...

33:31.050 --> 33:32.085
I'm okay.

33:34.380 --> 33:36.712
So, you should probably... Go.

33:36.890 --> 33:38.380
I, uh...

33:38.930 --> 33:41.216
I want to challenge your master.

33:42.640 --> 33:43.629
You wanna what?

33:45.100 --> 33:46.556
It's protocol.

33:47.400 --> 33:49.686
I visit your dojo,
I need to challenge your master.

33:50.940 --> 33:52.771
Wow. Well, okay...

33:53.240 --> 33:55.777
But I'm the master,
and I don't accept your challenge.

33:56.740 --> 33:58.150
Oh. Okay, um...

33:58.320 --> 34:00.982
Yeah, look, I'm closing up, so...

34:01.620 --> 34:04.327
Do you, uh...
Do you teach kung fu lessons?

34:05.960 --> 34:07.575
- Nope.
- You should.

34:07.750 --> 34:09.456
You'd probably get more students.

34:10.420 --> 34:11.660
I don't need the hassle.

34:12.630 --> 34:14.120
I could teach a couple of classes.

34:14.590 --> 34:18.253
I mean, that's what I was asking
when I was talking about work.

34:18.640 --> 34:20.631
I'd be cheap. No hassle at all.

34:21.510 --> 34:22.716
Where'd you train?

34:23.970 --> 34:24.971
K'un-Lun.

34:25.890 --> 34:27.846
Which is... Where?

34:28.020 --> 34:29.339
You, uh...

34:30.400 --> 34:31.810
Can't really get there from here.

34:32.940 --> 34:34.771
Nice try.
Now it's time to go.

34:36.110 --> 34:38.817
Well, if you...
You really need to leave.

34:40.620 --> 34:42.440
This is just a practice sword.

34:43.200 --> 34:44.326
It doesn't even have an edge.

34:44.500 --> 34:45.489
Trust me...

34:46.160 --> 34:48.116
You don't wanna know_ what it feels like to
have a practice sword

34:48.290 --> 34:49.826
smack you hard on the side of the face.

34:51.710 --> 34:52.950
I already do.

34:53.920 --> 34:55.581
Ask Master Lei Kung the Thunderer.

34:55.760 --> 34:57.159
I'm asking you...

34:57.720 --> 34:59.176
nicely...

34:59.590 --> 35:01.000
one last time.

35:01.800 --> 35:02.960
Please go.

35:05.640 --> 35:07.631
I apologise for any inconvenience.

35:15.360 --> 35:16.395
Hey!

35:28.040 --> 35:29.075
Thanks.

35:59.740 --> 36:01.401
You're the security guard from Rand.

36:01.660 --> 36:02.945
Why are you...

36:03.280 --> 36:04.486
Ow!

36:13.710 --> 36:14.699
Go.

39:19.560 --> 39:20.549
Ow!

39:22.650 --> 39:23.685
Who sent you?

39:24.570 --> 39:25.639
Who sent you?

39:27.400 --> 39:28.389
Ward Meachum.

40:13.200 --> 40:14.519
Hello, Shannon.

40:22.000 --> 40:23.126
Thank you.

40:37.560 --> 40:39.016
We have a situation.

40:40.350 --> 40:42.557
Something that we need to discuss
in person.

40:44.860 --> 40:46.680
I think it can wait until the morning.

40:50.320 --> 40:51.389
Of course.

40:51.860 --> 40:53.020
Right away.

42:50.610 --> 42:51.816
Hi, Dad.

42:52.440 --> 42:54.522
The Chinese yuan is gonna drop.

42:54.940 --> 42:58.444
- It's gonna affect our expansion there.
- I'll take care of it.

42:58.860 --> 43:01.943
Oh, like you're taking care
of the Danny Rand situation?

43:02.830 --> 43:04.445
How do you even know about that?

43:06.160 --> 43:07.149
Shit.

43:07.500 --> 43:08.785
Are you behind this?

43:09.250 --> 43:11.161
Is this another one of your stupid tests?

43:11.330 --> 43:12.786
No, Ward, I'm not behind it.

43:13.590 --> 43:15.455
I wish you'd take things like this
more seriously,

43:15.630 --> 43:17.370
so that I don't see my company destroyed.

43:17.550 --> 43:20.462
- So it's your company now?
- It's always been my company.

43:20.640 --> 43:22.380
You know, I could just ignore you.

43:22.550 --> 43:24.461
There's not a thing you could do about it.

43:24.640 --> 43:27.268
Oh, sometimes you still sound
like you're an eight-year-old.

43:27.430 --> 43:29.091
Yeah, yeah, Dad.

43:29.390 --> 43:31.187
I get the whole disappointed in me thing.

43:31.350 --> 43:32.681
You've been doing it my whole life.

43:32.860 --> 43:34.976
I expect more of you. That's all.

43:37.690 --> 43:39.692
Is he here all the time now?

43:40.860 --> 43:42.316
How much does he know?

43:42.660 --> 43:44.867
- What does it matter?
- I think you know why it matters.

43:47.330 --> 43:49.616
Ward, try to learn from me.

43:49.960 --> 43:52.121
You hire people when they're young,
single,

43:52.290 --> 43:55.202
looking for something to commit to,
to build their lives around.

43:56.170 --> 43:58.081
Pay 'em twice what they're worth.

43:59.010 --> 44:00.546
It builds loyalty.

44:01.550 --> 44:03.131
It's something I learned from Wendell.

44:03.300 --> 44:04.176
Sure.

44:04.350 --> 44:05.214
Kyle.

44:09.390 --> 44:12.439
Hey, will you ever betray me, Kyle?

44:12.600 --> 44:13.851
No, sir.

44:14.690 --> 44:16.180
You're a good man, Kyle.

44:17.900 --> 44:19.891
Why don't you take
the rest of the day off?

44:20.950 --> 44:22.190
It's nearly midnight, sir.

44:22.360 --> 44:24.021
Aw, too late then, huh?

44:25.530 --> 44:27.236
See? He loves me.

44:28.950 --> 44:30.201
Jesus, Dad.

44:31.210 --> 44:33.701
- What the hell is wrong with you?
- Never felt better.

44:35.250 --> 44:36.740
Of course.

44:39.880 --> 44:43.293
So... Let's talk about the real issue.

44:44.260 --> 44:46.592
This, uh, Danny Rand character.

44:46.760 --> 44:48.967
You tried to have Shannon handle it,
and that didn't work out so well.

44:49.140 --> 44:50.721
Apparently not.

44:50.890 --> 44:53.893
Hmm... So what's he saying?
What's his story?

44:54.600 --> 44:55.806
He sounds like a lunatic.

44:55.980 --> 44:57.356
I don't know what his story is.

44:57.650 --> 45:00.528
- You haven't talked to him?
- Well, no.

45:00.820 --> 45:02.640
I'm not gonna play his game.

45:08.240 --> 45:10.288
How the hell are we supposed
to deal with this guy

45:10.450 --> 45:11.610
if we don't know anything about him?

45:12.460 --> 45:14.246
Hey... Listen up.

45:14.500 --> 45:17.412
The first rule of war and business
IS to know your enemy.

45:17.590 --> 45:19.330
Yes, you've told me that,
but in this case...

45:19.500 --> 45:21.411
Have you considered this might be
someone hired

45:21.590 --> 45:24.332
to make us look bad
at a time we don't wanna look bad?

45:24.510 --> 45:26.466
Yes. Joy and I have been all through that.

45:26.640 --> 45:27.629
Yeah.

45:28.470 --> 45:33.260
Much trickier if this actually is young
Danny Rand come back to life.

45:34.810 --> 45:36.266
That's impossible.

45:37.900 --> 45:39.720
Stranger things have happened.

45:43.400 --> 45:44.560
If this is Danny...

45:44.740 --> 45:46.105
- Dad, come on.
- Think!

45:57.000 --> 45:59.127
If this is Danny...

46:00.500 --> 46:02.047
We can't let him go public.

46:02.590 --> 46:05.252
No. No, we cannot.

46:06.890 --> 46:09.882
Now, there are other questions
to consider as well.

46:11.810 --> 46:15.849
If he's still alive, does that mean
his parents are still alive?

46:16.640 --> 46:18.096
Who else knows he's alive?

46:18.400 --> 46:20.356
What does he know? Who has he told?

46:21.320 --> 46:23.641
How the hell did he learn martial arts?

46:26.320 --> 46:29.619
Why has he waited this long to show up?
Huh?

46:29.780 --> 46:33.329
And now that he's here...
What does he want?

46:34.500 --> 46:36.741
- I don't know.
- Neither do I.

46:36.920 --> 46:38.785
Which is why you can't just
send some idiot

46:38.960 --> 46:41.451
to beat the shit out of him. Understood?

46:42.920 --> 46:45.753
Now we need to approach this with finesse.

46:46.720 --> 46:48.585
Like the way you handle
everything in life?

46:48.760 --> 46:50.341
Don't be smart with me, Ward.

46:53.520 --> 46:54.669
Leave this to me.

46:55.560 --> 46:57.846
I'll tell you exactly what to do.

47:06.690 --> 47:08.692
Like always.

47:09.570 --> 47:10.776
Like always.

47:21.210 --> 47:23.121
Hey. Al, are you awake?

48:05.090 --> 48:07.502
"As long as the cycle of existence lasts,

48:08.970 --> 48:10.790
"may your happiness never decline.

48:14.510 --> 48:17.422
"May you attain the constant joy
of the bodhisattvas."

48:58.510 --> 49:00.637
How did you get in here?

49:01.810 --> 49:03.380
This was always my second home.

49:04.650 --> 49:05.799
I know all the ins and outs.

49:13.200 --> 49:14.849
Your brother tried
to have me killed last night.

49:15.910 --> 49:16.774
What?

49:17.370 --> 49:18.405
No.

49:19.700 --> 49:20.997
Can we finally talk?

49:24.500 --> 49:25.455
Okay.

49:25.960 --> 49:28.167
But... I have mace in my purse,

49:28.420 --> 49:30.160
and I can touch one button
and have a guard here.

49:32.720 --> 49:34.176
I'm not gonna hurt you.

49:40.430 --> 49:44.218
So... What makes you think
Ward tried to kill you?

49:44.390 --> 49:47.109
Which, by the way, sounds preposterous.

49:47.270 --> 49:49.181
